medical_history.chief_complaint: Ambiguous genitalia in a newborn infant.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: The patient was referred to the gender team on the first day of life, following an uncomplicated pregnancy and ultrasound that suggested a female gender. Physical examination revealed 46,XY DSD with notable findings.
medical_history.past_medical_history: Isolated 17,20-lyase deficiency due to a homozygous W27X mutation in the CYB5 gene.
medical_history.family_history: The patient is the first child of consanguineous parents; the family history was negative for sexual differentiation disorders.
